Secret Folk <br />
Hillman Rabble x4     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The fun part of this deck is watching your opponent gape when you put out 6 companions to start off. He&#39;ll probably start to snicker and laugh. The other fun part is beating him. <br />
Bid medium high, you want to go first and pull Aragorn. Exert anybody you like. The idea is to immediately, within the first two sites, set up a choke. Anything that gets by destroy it with Defent and Archery, if something still gets by use Aragorn with Swordsman. <br />
With Dunland, your objective is to control sites as fast as possible. Once you have about 3 sites controlled, use No Retreat to make him double-move, use Constantly Threatening to pull your Hillman Horde, and he&#39;s got about 5 huge guys who are all fierce and damage +1...and you skip the archery phase! Over the Isen lets you pick of some of the annoying smaller companions and then concetrate on the bigger ones. <br />
Believe it or not, this deck can win. YOu must MAKE SURE!! that all those 5 companions are dead by site 3. If he plays several minions, which he probably will because he&#39;ll have the pool, wipe them all out (but be careful) <br />
If this wins any tournements for you, give me all the praise and send me all your foils.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
